            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EUnclean%20was%20the%20word%20the%20Pharisees%20most%20feared.%20They%20spent%20hours%20washing%20pots%2C%20spots%2C%20and%20dots!%20They%20followed%20and%20amplified%20to%20impossible%20proportions%20every%20little%20hygienic%20requirement%20of%20the%20Mosaic%20Law.%20Jesus%20answered%20the%20objections%20of%20the%20Pharisees%20by%20pointing%20out%20that%20unclean%20refers%20more%20to%20a%20state%20of%20the%20heart%20than%20to%20a%20state%20of%20the%20hands.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBad%20attitudes%2C%20anger%2C%20adulteries%2C%20and%20arrogance%20cannot%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20human%20heart%20by%20any%20amount%20of%20hand%20washing.%20Unlike%20unclean%20foods%20that%20are%20simply%20processed%20through%20the%20body%20and%20the%20wastes%20removed%20naturally%2C%20unclean%20attitudes%20sit%20like%20poison%20in%20the%20human%20spirit%20and%20wait%20to%20spring%20into%20actions.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAaron%20learned%20the%20mystery%20of%20cleansing%20before%20God%3A%20%22Then%20he%20must%20dip%20his%20finger%20into%20the%20blood%20and%20sprinkle%20it%20seven%20times%20over%20the%20altar.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20he%20will%20cleanse%20it%20from%20Israel's%20defilement%20and%20return%20it%20to%20its%20former%20holiness%22%20(Leviticus%2016%3A19).%20Water%20may%20cleanse%20the%20body%2C%20but%20only%20blood%20can%20cleanse%20the%20spirit!%20Reach%20out%20and%20apply%20that%20blood%20to%20your%20spirit%20today.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
