d%20bathe%20yourself%20in%20water%2C%20and%20you%20will%20remain%20unclean%20until%20evening.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22levi_15_12%22%20bk%3D%22levi%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EAny%20clay%20pot%20the%20man%20touches%20must%20be%20broken%2C%20and%20any%20wooden%20utensil%20he%20touches%20must%20be%20rinsed%20with%20water.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22levi_15_13%22%20bk%3D%22levi%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhen%20the%20man%20with%20the%20discharge%20is%20healed%2C%20he%20must%20count%20off%20seven%20days%20for%20the%20period%20of%20purification.%20Then%20he%20must%20wash%20his%20clothes%20and%20bathe%20himself%20in%20fresh%20water%2C%20and%20he%20will%20be%20ceremonially%20clean.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22levi_15_14%22%20bk%3D%22levi%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EOn%20the%20eighth%20day%20he%20must%20get%20two%20turtledoves%20or%20two%20young%20pigeons%20and%20come%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20at%20the%20entrance%20of%20the%20Tabernacle%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E15%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ETent%20of%20Meeting%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2015%3A29.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20give%20his%20offerings%20to%20the%20priest.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22levi_15_15%22%20bk%3D%22levi%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20priest%20will%20offer%20one%20bird%20for%20a%20sin%20offering%20and%20the%20other%20for%20a%20burnt%20offering.%20Through%20this%20process%2C%20the%20priest%20will%20purify%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E15%3A15%3C